    "context": "A cha chaan teng (茶餐廳) is HK's working-class diner. Fast, loud, cash-only. The waiter has heard worse Cantonese than yours. Just point and speak.",
    "cultural_note": "Cha chaan tengs (茶餐廳) were born in the 1950s when the working class wanted Western café culture without the prices. They built a menu that mixed everything: HK-style milk tea brewed through a cloth filter for a silky texture (nicknamed \"silk stocking tea\"), Spam on toast, borscht that bears little resemblance to Ukrainian borscht, and scrambled eggs on macaroni. The result is uniquely and irrevocably Hong Kong.",
